Sentencas: (CDC) powders as the anode materials of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) were prepared by sol-gel method.

Sentencas: The NiO-CDC anode-supported cells were fabricated by dry-pressing process using Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta (GDC) as electrolyte and La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (LSCF) - Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta(GDC) as cathode.
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Cobalt-Doped Ceria (CDC) for IT-SOFCs Anodes in Natural Gas

Sentencas: The crystal structure, morphology and chemical stability were investigated by XRD and SEM respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Cobalt-Doped Ceria (CDC) for IT-SOFCs Anodes in Natural Gas

Sentencas: The performances of single cells were tested by using humidified natural gas (3% H2O) as fuel and oxygen as oxidant in the temperature range from 400 degrees C to 700 degrees C.

Sentencas: The results show that the anode of the cell has good open-framework; The 50% NiO-50% Ce0.8Co0.2Oy (C20C80) anode-supported cell shows the best electrochemical performance among the eight cells composed of different anodes.
